The paper deals with the problem of inverse reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses a simulated robotic application, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of hidden variables in the method suggests that it may also be relevant to the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the application of the method to a robotic vision task suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant category. However, given the focus on machine learning and the use of maximum entropy IRL, we believe that cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories.
